column11: From which country do you participate in the survey?
column16: Please select your Facebook usage type:
column17: How often do you use Facebook?
column18: Do you know/aware of the privacy policy rules of Facebook?
column19: Have you configured the privacy setting of your profile?
column20: Do you know that you can control the visibility of your posts with some privacy settings? (restricting the visibility of your post to only all/some of your friends, friends and friends of friends, or public)?
column21: What is your general preference for the visibility of your posts?
column22: Suppose that you have commented on a post that was created by your best friend and that this post is only shared by your best friends' friends. You trust that your friend will not make your comment visible to others than the selected group of people. However, after few days your best friend changes the privacy setting of this post to public. As a result of Facebook Privacy Policy (stating that privacy of interactions on a post only depends on the privacy setting of that particular post, controlled tuned only by the post owner), your comment became visible to public, without getting your approval. What is your opinion about this policy?
column23: Suppose that you see a public post in Facebook, and comment on it, by being aware that your comment will be visible to everyone. After a while, suppose that the post owner changed the visibility of that post to friends only, and you're not among his/her list of friends on Facebook. As a result of the Facebook Privacy Policy as described previously, you cannot see the post. You cannot even have access to your own comment or see it in your own action logs. What is your opinion about this policy?
column24: Were you aware of above described privacy related issues?
column25: Do you think that our solution is clearly understood through the mockup?
column26: Do you think that this solution is useful to improve the privacy awareness of Facebook members?
column27: Do you think that this solution can be implemented in real world? If so, by whom?
column28: Do you think that this problem should be solved by Facebook through policy regulations and service refinements?
column29: Do you have any other comments, questions, or concerns?
